<subSubSection id="2C2AEF47A6B095B397DC1B73564F7121" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1C77102B21076F8C006731FFD053E09B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4392FCAC7C4D7357924738B636C4C135" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to the southern part of the Baja California peninsula, where it grows on rocky slopes in dry deciduous forest around 500-600 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8A42087A2C6660B089A4508F8557F30" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="E6666D388DC4E801821307CF95A352B8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Baja California Sur</emphasis>
: Sierra de la Giganta, Valle de Arroyo Hondo, 
<emphasis id="0394ABB17F5F35A3A94391F0121A374C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Carter</emphasis>
5007 (BM), 5620 (BM, MICH, MO, UC); sine data, 
<emphasis id="11C78CE382BF5BB8D956495618CA41E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M.L. Diguet</emphasis>
(P).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="228D4BB36E0297B033BA28FD85CBE364" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F5F6A54D45EF78AEE28C3D2DBDF90566" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0101E6E7F0EB7A34B2C9AB0CE03716FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="64D7E83711BFD795DD4EE604DB339F3C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tastensis">
<emphasis id="8D8DD2669BFA3DB3C897791064851039" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea tastensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the corolla much smaller and the stamens included.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
